# TypeScript & API usage

- Prefer **zero `as any`**. Derive types from `src/integrations/supabase/types.ts` or narrow with `unknown`.
- Every **`supabase.from()` / RPC** result: handle **`error`**; do not assume `data` is set.

```ts
const { data, error } = await supabase.from("…").select();
if (error) {
  toast.error("Failed to load. Please try again.");
  return;
}
```

- Async paths: `try/catch` or `.catch()`; avoid silent failures.
- Props: explicit interfaces/types for components; avoid implicit `any`.

## Known debt (tighten over time)
Heavy `as any` history in files such as `InvoiceReview.tsx`, `EnterInventory.tsx`, `ListManagement.tsx` — new code should not add to this pattern.

## Structure (aspirational)
Prefer shared query/helpers in `src/lib/` or `src/services/` for repeated Supabase access; large pages may still inline queries — match existing file style when editing.

## Code hygiene
Avoid leaving commented-out dead code. Prefer structured logging or error boundaries over stray `console.log` in user-facing flows. Split components that grow far past ~300 lines when you are already touching them.
